The paper proposes a new model for controlling gradient flow in feed-forward networks applied to computer vision tasks, specifically image captioning using the MSCOCO dataset. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with machine learning and computer vision tasks. The use of recurrent networks also suggests that cs.CL is a likely category. Finally, the focus on gradient control and optimization suggests that cs.NE and cs.AI are also possible categories.
